// f_pcre_replace_callback() (src/packages/pcre/pcre.cc) allocated its
// substrings array via pcre_get_substrings() *before* validating the
// third argument, so passing the documented "no callback" sentinel (0)
// on a pattern with capture groups took the error() path without ever
// freeing that array -- a deterministic per-call leak. This just
// exercises the path for a clean, catchable error; the leak itself is
// verified separately (build with the fix reverted and compare
// LeakSanitizer output across a run exercising this call many times).
void do_tests() {
    mixed err = catch(pcre_replace_callback("ab", "(a)(b)", 0));
    ASSERT(err);
}
